I listened to the Electron launch through my big sound system (each speaker cabinet has 2 18 in wolfers, a midrange horn, and 4 piezoelectric tweeters).  The rocket ignition was quite awsome!  But, here's a question, even after the rocket got out of what should've been audible range, I could still hear a rumbling noise through the rocket's entire powered ascent, even through second stage cutoff.  That should've been way out of range of the microphones.  Why was I hearing this continuous rumbling?  It didn't start until the liftoff.

There's far too much stuttering and corrections followed by sorry, so it just makes a company that needs to prove themselves to the world, not look that professional :(
